<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">📖 Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">Turn your plan into a public piece, without hiding the trade-off to do it.</p>
  <p>You turn your plan into two public-facing things: a live activity that teaches other students the choice your neighbourhood faces, and a shareable artifact (a map-based infographic, a carousel, or a short captioned video) for the school's environmental showcase. Here is the design tension worth naming: public outreach rewards a clean, confident message, but the rubric rewards naming what you sacrificed. So the artifact has to be built so the trade-off stays visible (to get this, we gave up that), or the public format quietly undercuts the very thinking the unit is testing. You also plan for consent and an opt-out, because anything shared publicly needs a non-public fallback.</p>
  <p class="sub" style="color: var(--muted);">Full block content lands in the Unit 6 deep build. The consent model and the exact public channels are open decisions in the rework brief.</p>
</section>

